{"_id":"24961f3713b7515d","name":"CyberSquirt","type":"cyberware","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-visor-technological.webp","system":{"grade":"standard","essence_cost":0,"installed":false,"category":"bodyware","cost":1400,"availability":"","street_index":2,"mods":{},"description":"The cyberSquirt fires up to 10 shots at a time of chemical/biological agents in a special gelling agent. Like the non-cybered Ares Squirt. the cyberSquirt holds 10 chemical rounds and the gel reservoir holds enough gel for up to 20 shots. The reservoir must be reloaded once for every 2 cartridge reloads. The gel is made of DMSO (dimethyl sulfoxide), a utility chemical that forces the skin to absorb delivered chem - Ical/biological agents. Porous armor, such as armor clothing and Kevlar weaves, offers no protection against DMSO. Rigid armor (higher than 5, or plated) applies half its normal Defensive Rating (rounded up) against DMSO attacks. (See p. 92, Shadowtech, for effects of DMSO.)"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"shadowrun2e"}}
{"_id":"6d3fd4959f88311b","name":"CyberTorso","type":"cyberware","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-visor-technological.webp","system":{"grade":"standard","essence_cost":1.5,"installed":false,"category":"bodyware","cost":120000,"availability":"","street_index":1,"mods":{"body":1},"description":"The cybertorso and cyberskull each add +1 to the character's Body Attribute. The cybertorso also reduces by half (round up) the additional Essence cost of Strength or Quickness enhancements beyond 3 points (see Limb Enhancements, p. 31, and Cyberware Rules, p. 49)."},"folder":null,"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"shadowrun2e"}}
